  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of making illegally-obtained money appear legal by passing it through complex financial transactions. Legally, it typically involves three stages:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Concealing the source of the money through complex transactions\n3. Integration: Reintroducing the \"cleaned\" money into legitimate economic activities\n\nKey legal elements usually include:\n- Knowingly concealing the origins of illegally obtained money\n- Attempting to make unlawful funds appear legitimate\n- Engaging in financial transactions designed to hide the source of funds\n- Transferring money to disguise its illegal origins\n\nSpecific definitions can vary between jurisdictions, but most countries criminalize money laundering under financial crime statutes.",
